## üõë Stop Services

```bash
# Stop all containers
docker compose down

# Stop and remove volumes (WARNING: deletes all data)
docker compose down -v
```

## üèóÔ∏è Production Build

### Build Frontend Docker Image
```bash
docker build \
    --build-arg ENVIRONMENT=production \
    --build-arg KEYCLOAK_URL=http://your-domain.com \
    --build-arg API_URL=http://your-domain.com/api \
    -t your-dockerhub/dechet-frontend \
    -f frontend/Dockerfile \
    frontend
```

### Build Backend Docker Image
```bash
docker build \
    -t your-dockerhub/dechet-backend \
    -f backend/Dockerfile \
    backend
```

### Run Full Stack with Docker Compose
```bash
# Set environment variables in .env file
docker compose up -d
```

## üîß Troubleshooting

### Keycloak realm not imported
If users cannot log in, the realm might not have imported:
```bash
docker compose restart keycloak
# Wait 30 seconds, then check http://localhost:8080
```

### Frontend build errors
Clear Angular cache:
```powershell
cd frontend
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .angular -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
npm start
```

### Backend connection errors
Ensure infrastructure is running:
```bash
docker ps
# Should show mongo, postgres, keycloak, mongo-express running
```

## ü§ñ Automated Incident Reporting (n8n Workflow)

The system includes an n8n workflow that automates incident reporting via email:

### Features
- **Email Monitoring**: Automatically monitors Gmail for citizen incident reports
- **AI-Powered Extraction**: Uses Groq AI to extract structured incident data from emails
- **Duplicate Detection**: Checks MongoDB for similar incidents using AI similarity matching
- **Smart Responses**: 
  - If duplicate detected (‚â•75% similarity): Sends automated reply to citizen
  - If new incident: Notifies admin and creates incident record

### Workflow Location
`workflows/incident_report.json`

### Setup Requirements
- n8n instance with the workflow imported
- Gmail OAuth2 credentials configured
- Groq API credentials for AI processing
- MongoDB connection for duplicate detection

### How It Works
1. Gmail trigger monitors incoming emails every minute
2. AI agent extracts incident details (description, location, priority)
3. Duplicate check compares against existing incidents in MongoDB
4. Conditional logic routes to appropriate response:
   - **Duplicate found**: Reply to citizen with confirmation
   - **New incident**: Notify admin and process new report

